The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 A Chinese outfit will be the foreign team of the 112th IFA Shield, which gets underway next Monday. Shenzen Football Team will be paired with two local giants Mohun Bagan and Mohammedan Sporting in Group B, while East Bengal, Mahindra United and Sporting Clube de Goa comprise Group A. 

 The tournament kicks off with the Mohun Bagan-Mohammedan Sporting encounter. The dates for semi-finals and final have been tentatively fixed for December 13 and 15, respectively. It will be finalised in consultation with the tournaments telecast rights holders ESPN-Star Sports on Wednesday. Incidentally, all matches will be shown live. 

 Mohun Bagan physio Robson Mattos de Oliviera on Tuesday was appointed as the clubs interim coach after Biswajit Bhattacharya resigned following Durand Cup failure.

 According to a club official, a full-time coach will soon be announced. It has been learnt that Chima Okerie is in the forefront while the old faces like Subrata Bhattacharya and Aloke Mukherjee are also in the fray. 

 Calcutta Port Trust routed their Chennai counterparts 4-1 in the All India Major Ports Football Meet on Tuesday. Sujit Dey scored a brace for the winners. In other matches, Mormugao beat Vizag 4-1, Tuticorin defeated Paradip 3-0 and Cochin got the better of Mumbai 2-0. 

 B. Samants unbeaten 131 helped Andhra take Day I initiatives against Bengal in their Cooch Behar Trophy match on Tuesday. 

 CRICKET: Cooch Behar Trophy: Bengal vs Andhra at JU Salt Lake campus from 9.30 am. 

 GOLF: East India Ladies Championship at Tollygunge Club. 




